<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98648797693814>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Lava Storm</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 12:26 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Lavastorm is one of the nicest, safest places for a magician to fight in from level 12-16. After level 16, it gets really rough because you don't have a new anti-summon spell until level 20 (I think) and your new direct-damage spells up until level 24 are all fire-based, and Lavastorm mobs are pretty much immune to fire.<br><br>You did buy the invisibility spell at level 8, right? That's all you need to get to Lavastorm. Invis yourself right before you get to the EC/Nektalus zone border, then take a left after zoning and keep to the zone border until you get to the Lavastorm zone. You can bind yourself deep in the tunnel with little risk, though be wary that some groups like to use this area as a staging ground for fighting the Dark Elf guards and the wandering golem-type guards in the area.<br><br>Inside Lavastorm, all you really have to watch for are the wandering Fire Elementals. At level 14, some of these will be green while others are red...that's a huge level range, so be sure to consider all the mobs. If you decide to fight an elemental, pull it with Cancel Magic to remove the damage shield, then use your anti-summon spell while your pet bashes away.<br><br>The fire drakes are still pretty good experience at level 14, and excellent loot given how easy they are. Lava basilisks are also good experience and loot (those are NOT 8 copper eggs; they sell for about 6gp apiece!). Rock dervishes are also good experience and loot, and since they hit fairly often, they make an excellent target for your fireshielded pet. Use your summoned bags to carry the bricks of ore, and make frequent trips to the gypsies to sell them for about 4gp apiece.<br><br>With the exception of the fire elementals (which wander, so always be wary of them) and the crocodiles (which do not wander, so just stay away from their little corner), few of the mobs in this zone are aggressive or social, so it is an incredibly save zone to fight in. For safety, just in case, you can set up a kill zone near the Nektalus or Najena zone.<br><br>If you get a little bored of the typical Lavastorm mobs, you get together a small pickup group and go do the entrance area to Najena, or go camp one of the goblin camps...just be wary of an Erudite necromancer NPC who will unleash all kinds of havoc if she spawns. Thankfully, she never wanders unless pulled, and the goblins seldom leave their perch. When they do, they are easily solod and can drop some pretty decent loot as well.<br><br>All in all, this is an excellent zone for your teenaged mage to fight in, with very good loot. You can also start picking up your research words here; follow the research links on this page to find out what words you should be saving and what to auction off to necromancers.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>2 Replies</td></tr>
